Our Annual sports fest!!!
We are now open for registrations and we want you to come and join us in the first-ever virtual Protathlitis tournament.
As the pandemic has affected all of our outdoor activities, one thing that it can't ever stop is our will to get out again and give it our best - for our respective teams, our supporters, and most of all, for ourselves.
To keep this fire of spirit burning within all of us, we have devised an innovative format for this year's Protathlitis.

17/05/2021, 19:18 - +91 91114 44550: Hey! 

I am Volunteering with Muskurahat Foundation, an NGO based in Mumbai. 

*Project KEYtaab*, an initiative by Muskurahat Foundation, aims at providing the underprivileged children from Shelter Homes and orphanages with the holistic development that they lack. 

Through a specially crafted curriculum we are trying to give them a right *Upbringing*, which they do not get *21st century life skills* like critical thinking and problem solving among many others, and improve their emotional well-being through *Therapy*. 

We are working with 450 children currently, in 11 shelter homes/orphanages, across 3 cities. 

*Donate and help us launch the project in 15 more cities, transforming the lives of 1000+ children*.

To know more, please visit www.muskurahat.org.in

Please donate by going on this link: https://donate.muskurahat.org.in/?r=anu8532

Referral Code: anu8532
(Please keep in mind to check the reference code while donating. It will help me track my efforts.)

Brushes To Pixels, the Art Club of SIT, is organizing its first ever competition since the club came into force.

On 6th June 1674, at Raigad fort, Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj was crowned as the King of Maratha Swaraj. 
So for this auspicious occasion, we are holding a *fun competition* in which the participants have to upload an artwork related to Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj in the google form link given below. 
All art forms are encouraged for this competition. 

*The link shall be valid till 6th June 2021, 11:59pm.*

*Google Form Link*: https://forms.gle/YuhF2f3SYUGQ2d7w8

The winner of this competition shall be featured on the Brushes To Pixels Instagram Page!

We hope to receive a large number of entries! 

_*Let’s together keep the magic of art alive!*_

23/07/2021, 09:32 - Riya Ganguli: *FOR DIVISION A,*
*You are to solve these numerical and ask your doubts (if any) to Sushma ma’am (on text)*

1. A single-phase auto-transformer has a voltage ratio 320V:250 V and supplies a load of 20 kVA at 250V. Assuming an ideal transformer, determine the current in each section of the winding

2. A voltage transformer has 4000 primary turns and 20 secondary turns. If the voltmeter reading in the secondary shows 110V , how much is the voltage at the primary winding?

3. A transformer has a primary coil and a secondary coil with the number of loops are 500 and 5000. Input voltage is 220 V. What is the output voltage?

4. A transformer has primary coil with 1200 loops and secondary coil with 1000 loops. If the current in the primary coil is 4 Ampere, then what is the the current in the secondary coil.

5. A 2000/200V, 20kVA transformer has 66 turns in the secondary. Calculate: a) Primary turns b) primary and secondary full load currents. Is the transformer step up? Why?

6. An ideal 25kVA transformer has 500 turns on the primary winding and 40 turns on the secondary winding. The primary is connected to 3000 volt, 50 Hz supply. Calculate: a) Primary and secondary currents on full load b) secondary voltage c) the maximum core flux Is the transformer step down? Why?

17/08/2021, 17:47 - +91 91114 44550: Good evening. 
We at the SIT Photography Club are honoured to have two brilliant astrophotographers, Prathamesh Jaju and Aditya Kinjawadekar, among us to explain the fascinating science and techniques behind a very specific type of photography: 
  *Astrophotography.*

In this delightfully interactive and informative session, they are going to take us on a journey, explaining the various concepts of astronomy involved while setting up that perfect shot to capture a wonder in the night sky. From the basics of astrophotography, to the special equipment and necessary physiological conditions required. 

In addition, they are going to explain in detail some specific types of astrophotography, such as deepsky, multi-wavelength, planetary as well as lunar astrophotography.

On the occasion of World Photography Day, join us on this journey on our spaceship Earth, on the 19th of August, 7 pm.
The link below will give you further directives. See you there!

27/08/2021, 11:25 - +91 96731 09542: Dear all 
The major points from today's HoDs meeting 

All the students should be vaccinated at least one dose else they will not be allowed  to attend the physical classes. 

 If they are affected with covid , they should  submit the COVID +VE certificate

 All Saturdays as per norms 1st and 4th Saturday holidays,  2nd and 3rd Saturday will be working day.

 Biometric attendance will be followed for the faculty members from September 1st onwards

 The students those who are staying in hostel, they  need to pay 50 % of the hostel fee 35000/-

Second years and final years will be attending the physical classes from September 1st onwards.

For the final years the theory  classes will be handled or  placement training will be followed for all the days. Final year will be in the campus for the entire semester 

 For the second years initially they need to complete the lab classes .  after completing the lab classes , theory classes may be followed 

After certain period second years will be sent home and the classes will be handled online.

After second years,  third years will be called for physical classes. 

For the third years,  the lab classes may be handled  after the physical reopening for them. Till that only theory classes may be handled.

Just kidding...Go attend your Online classes🤓

30/08/2021, 21:40 - Aditya Rane: Hey Guys!
Hope you all are doing well... 
On this auspicious day of Krishna Janmashtami, me and my friends are starting a club - *"Spirituality for Youth"* in SIT. Our institute is helping us develop academically in many ways, but many a times we also must evolve *mentally* to attain our goals. Thus, the founding of this club. 
Since self-development and spirituality come hand in hand, we will include self-development activities in this club such as: sessions on *values* and ethics, *social etiquette* and much more.
This club will help students:
1.	Deal with *loneliness, discontent* 
2.	Stay away from *narcotics* 
3.	Deal with *depression* 
4.	Find themselves
5.	Deal with *anxiety* 
6.	Handle *competition* 
This club is versatile and can be joined by students from *any religion* .
What we as the members of this club will do:
1.	Organise online spiritual lectures for students and for the youth.
2.	Post self-development articles on our social media handle.
3.	Conduct basic meditation sessions.
4.	Nature walks
5.	Orphanage and old age home visits
 *Objective* : Teaching students to lead a fruitful life.
Students come to college to excel in all areas of their life; we are already excelling academically; we can also excel mentally and spiritually.
This club is *NOT* official in SIT as of now, but we have been promised that as our members increase and activities are conducted on a regular basis it will become official.
Trust me, this club is going to be a lot of fun, we will be doing many activities together.
Here is the link to join the WhatsApp group: https://chat.whatsapp.com/IlkHVXGMeQY0iqV3BYLKRu

20/09/2021, 22:02 - Neeraj Tonsalli: *Charge up your batteries and feel the electricity course through your veins.* 🏁🏎

Ever dreamt of making a race car? If yes, WWR's annual recruitment is here for you. Wrench Wielders Racing, the Formula Student team of SIT would like to invite all motorheads to one of the most exciting endeavours any engineer can undertake, making a race car. Join us in our journey to design, simulate, build and race our car from scratch each year at national and international events and strive to improve our automobile knowledge and experience while inching towards perfection. We believe in speed, ingenuity and tirelessly work towards success. 
With both Combustion Vehicle as well as an Electric Vehicle in the team, we would love to have intelligent and hard-working souls onboard with us to shape our vision of making a racing beast. The electrical departments include: 
• Battery Pack Design
• Embedded systems
• Power electronics
• Wired and Wireless Communications
• AI and data analysis
• PCB design and analysis
• Embedded hardware and software design
• Data Acquisition
• Electric Drive
Not to count the numerous mechanical and CS/IT departments that one can opt for. 
Being a part of the team pushes one to learn and properly utilize software such as MATLAB, Scilab, kicad, altium, eagle, microcap, zuken Ecadstar, zuken E3, embedded C/C++  etc. In short there is no end to the amount of knowledge the team offers.  On top of all these the team opens up the opportunity to attend international Webinars and workshops from the Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE), Formula Student Germany (FSG) etc.  
We also have non-technical departments for which we are recruiting, namely- finance, team management, sponsorship, social media/website management and business. 
The only prerequisite is a burning passion within, for the field. That’s right no prior in-depth knowledge required in engineering or business.  
Think you’ve got the what it takes to be a *Race car Engineer*? 
Interested students are requested to fill this form:
https://forms.gle/L27TGByA668yt1rH7
For more information you may contact the following:
*Archit Vanikar: +91 8552045557*
*Shivansh Lolayekar: +91 9767172184* 

We also encourage you to follow us on Instagram for further updates:
*@wrenchwieldersracing*
https://www.instagram.com/wrenchwieldersracing/?hl=en

10/10/2021, 20:25 - +91 99209 51882: 1) A mail was sent earlier regarding the online ESE. Taking that into consideration, students have already made plans for Diwali and post Diwali.  
2) Given Diwali break, most students will reach post Diwali, which means multitudes of students and their parents will reach campus in a very short time span. This could cause an outbreak of the virus. A phased manner opening would reduce the chances of that happening. 
3) Pune airports will remain closed from 16th to 30th October due to runway maintenance by IAF. So travelling during this time will be restricted for most of the students. Reaching Mumbai/nagpur and then going to Pune is not feasible either. 
4) The email sent mentions that all classes will be in offline mode starting 8th November, but a student reaching on 7th November will have to be under quarantine for a week. Which means they'll miss their classes despite being in the campus. 
5) Re-opening post end semester exams, during the break after semester would be preferable as students will need some time to settle in and will have less academic pressure in the beginning of semester. 
5) Kerala has seen a spike in covid cases recently, if someone gets affected on their way to campus, it'll be a disaster as the entire campus will be under a bubble. 
5) Due to COVID protocols, hostel rooms will have restrictions, not everyone will get a room in the campus, making arrangements for accomodation will require time for students coming from others states, which will be easier during mid sem break. 
6) Online teaching and offline examination might hinder the students academically.
7) The students have to be doubly vaccinated in order to attend classes. There are many students who will have their second dose during mid November and will end up missing classes. 
8) if for some reasons, a student is not able to make it to the college, they'll not only miss on classes but also on labwork. Starting in phased manner and complete offline mode in next semester would ensure no one misses out on this.
9) Other colleges have followed a similar path of hybrid mode to reduce burden on students. 
10) It's logistically an issue as well to ensure that the student reaches the campus  completely equipped.

Calling out to all the dancers out there, If you’re interested in putting on your dancing shoes and being a member of our crew we invite you to showcase your talent to us.

The auditions are open to all the batches! 

To audition, please keep the following things in mind : 

1. Prepare and submit a video of 2-3 minutes of your dance routines. 
2. Any dance form is acceptable. 
3. The choreography can be your own or implemented from someone else’s. 
4. Make sure your movements are visible and the audio is absolutely clear.
 
And lastly, dance to have fun! Let us get a glance of your style and skills alongside your confidence and expressions. 

Submit your videos along with your details on the below mentioned link by 25th October 2021. 

https://tinyurl.com/S2SAuditions
For further enquiries contact us at 8800989356  or DM us directly on @soul_to_sole_sit. 

Best of Luck! 👏🏻

Syllabus:    Unit 2 :   Introduction of Combinational logic circuits , adders, subtractions (Half and Full),Binary parallel adder, BCD adder, look-ahead carry adder, Code conversion  (Binary to gray , gray to binary, binary to BCD) ,Comparators (1 bit, 2 - bit, 4- bit ), parity generation. Encoders (Octal to Binary, Decimal to BCD), decoders, Multiplexer, Demultiplexer, Multivariable function implementation using MUX & decoder. Unit 3 :  Introduction of  Sequential logic circuit ,Classification, Latches and flip-flop (FF) FF operating characteristics, clock skew and time race, Clocked S-R, J-K,M/S J-K, T and D F/F, race around condition, Flip-flop truth table, excitation table, flip-flop conversion.

    
NOTE: 

1. Class Test will start at 12:05 p.m. (sharp). The test will be of 60 minutes. You are required to submit your responses well within the time otherwise Microsoft forms will not accept your response after 01.05 PM.  


2. This test will be conducted using  Microsoft Forms. Make sure, you have an appropriate login of the Microsoft Teams, proper internet connection during the test. No re-test will be conducted if you fail to appear/submit this test.

Greetings from Team Compendium 5.2 👋

Every semester, The Department of Electronics and Telecommunication publishes an exciting newsletter that highlights the semester's events while also providing a _space for articles of various genres_. ⚡

We are looking forward to *articles, blogs, artworks of varied interests, and not just technological trends that you would like to share with the whole SIT community*. ✒️

*Students and professors that are interested can fill out this Google form and submit their entries.*
_https://forms.gle/SxwdjiujQj2UB5jy9_
We hope you all would like to contribute to this year’s compendium and share your compositions and accomplishments with us. ✌🏻
*PS: Please make sure that you submit your own content and not something from the internet so that the newsletter is engaging for all the readers.*

19/08/2022, 15:02 - +91 96694 88071: Dear all,
I hope your day has started wonderfully. To top it all off, I'm thrilled to inform you that the SIT Finance Club has officially been launched.

What sets us apart from other clubs in existence?
 The club intends to function by an open conversation session model, which implies that we'd like to encourage open dialogue sessions to develop knowledge and turn them into social media posts if someone has a novel idea, quotation, or topic to discuss.
• How many of us, for example, are familiar with terms like EBITDA, the distinction between trading and investing, and mutual funds? What is the bare minimum SIP? Discussions might begin with such a straightforward subject.
Moving on to economic indicators, exchange-traded funds, taxes, investment tactics, etc.

Check the PPT for more details. 

With a lot more to offer and beat the monotony and galvanize your economic interest, we are here. 
Fill in the google form ASAP and we would love to welcome you aboard.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf5lpb0WH9_CGsJGvBOH3CLtzkUXu-E4wcy9mXuqyGenzp8Jg/viewform


With warm regards,
Team Economic Society.

07/09/2022, 11:57 - +91 99209 51882: Greetings!

Fun fact: The E&TC department on the third floor of our cherished building published the first-ever official newsletter of SIT. This newsletter eventually earned the name "Compendium." From last year, COMPENDIUM 5.2 now rechristened as VIDAYAM is now open to students and faculty members of All Branches!

Each year, the most deserving individuals get this distinguished newsletter, which now represents the talent of the entire campus. It is now time to turn it over to the 2020–24 batch, together with enthusiastic volunteers from previous batches. Can you make this newsletter better than ever before? 

We are looking for a diverse team of editors, designers, and photographers to take this newsletter forward. One among you talented contenders would be chosen as the head of VIDAYAM!
Are you willing to be a part of this team? If yes, then fill out this google form by the 10th of September.
https://forms.gle/5H78RfR8j34zTzr3A

A brief interview would be conducted for the interested candidates, the details of which would be conveyed later.

Hoping to interact with you soon!

Regards

Saijal Singhal
Head, VIDAYAM
